The paper deals with a communication system using spread spectrum techniques, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The focus of the paper is on anti-jamming techniques, which is a common problem in communication systems and falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The proposed receiver also involves signal processing and optimization techniques, which can be categorized under systems and control (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
